text=%3c%3c|Macropedia/ImperiumEquipmentIndex|>>%0a%0a%0a!! Enhanced Soldier Systems%0a%0aBack in the days of the [[Terran Republic]] and [[ImperiumMacropediaTimeline|Early Imperium]] plenty of people with "pure" Terran ancestry had deep-seated fears of genetic enhancement. Confronted by the obvious physical superiority of some [[Anthorph]] breeds, they were psychologically impelled to take compensatory risks.%0a%0aMilitary designers worked on artificial methods of producing a super-soldier. In addition to the wide variety of drugs and powered-armor systems that appeared and quickly failed, the Enhanced Soldier Systems briefly held some sway.%0a%0aAn ESS embeds electronic nodes within the neural pathways of the subject. This can be done with several purposes in mind. Pre-eminently, the reflexes and dexterity of the subject are superficially increased. Secondarily, ports can also be installed to link the subject with Powered Armor, or a jury-rigged [[Raptor Combat Suit]]. Although "cybermadness" was a popular storyline in the period, it was not so much the problem as neurological degeneration.%0a%0aAn ESS also requires relatively frequent maintenance surgeries to maintain its healthy operation. Since many veterans began to resent them, the ESS gained a poor political reputation. They have maintained a presence in the underworld and among various sundry groups, including a few "Pure Terran" Mercenery groups.%0a%0aESS's enjoyed a brief return to the limelight for the [[Zenbrudi War]], but have generally fallen out of use among reputable military and combat services.%0a%0a!! References%0a# [[Anthorph]]s%0a# [[Zenbrudi War]]%0a%0a%0a%0a!! Related Articles%0a(:pagelist group=Macropedia fmt=simple {$Name}:)%0a%0a%0a[[!ImperiumEquipment]] [[!BorisHelfsteinAuthored]][[!Medical Equipment]]
